[small][b]Security Interest:[/b] Borrower grants Lender a continuing, first-priority security interest in the collateral above, including proceeds, replacements, and insurance payouts, until all obligations are satisfied. Borrower waives any requirement for prior notice before set-off or freeze actions.[/small]
[hr][b]5. Borrower Representations & Covenants (Strict)[/b]
[list]
[*]Borrower confirms all provided information is accurate; any error is treated as a material misrepresentation.
[*]Borrower agrees to maintain uninterrupted contact routing (NET/holopad/fax) and respond to Idris notices within 2 hours.
[*]Borrower agrees not to sell, gift, transfer, conceal, or “lose” collateral items while obligations remain outstanding.
[*]Borrower agrees to keep an Idris account open, in good standing, and funded for auto-debit at all times.
[*]Borrower agrees to non-disparagement regarding Idris Incorporated and to keep contract terms confidential unless disclosure is legally compelled.
[/list]
[hr][b]6. Default Events (Broad / Accelerated)[/b]
[small]Any of the following constitutes “Default” immediately and without grace:[/small]
[list]
[*]Any failed or reversed debit for any reason (including insufficient funds, account lock, network interruption, or user refusal).
[*]Any payment received late (after scheduled debit time) or in an amount less than required.
[*]Any material misrepresentation, omission, or inconsistent identity/account information.
[*]Any attempt to close, shield, split, transfer, or otherwise hinder access to authorized accounts.
[*]Any impairment of collateral (loss, damage, concealment, refusal to surrender, or disputed ownership).
[*]Failure to respond to Idris contact attempts within 2 hours.
[*]“Reputational Harm”: public disparagement, sabotage of servicing, or inducing others to breach their obligations.
[*]Any other condition specified here: [field]
[/list]
[hr][b]7. Remedies & Collection (Punitive)[/b]
[small]Upon Default, Lender may, without waiving other remedies and without further notice:[/small]
[list]
[*]Accelerate the debt (full outstanding balance immediately due).
[*]Apply a Default APR of 89.9% (daily compounding) from the moment of Default.
[*]Post a Default Administration Charge of 2,500 CR immediately.
[*]Freeze, restrict, or set-off funds from authorized accounts up to the amount owed (including fees/costs).
[*]Seize collateral or instruct custodians/employers to surrender collateral and/or wages.
[*]Charge “Recovery Costs” equal to 35% of the total balance, plus itemized expenses, plus a 5,000 CR “Reclamation Mobilization Fee” if recovery is dispatched.
[*]Assign the matter to Idris recovery services or contracted agents for debt reclamation and asset recovery.
[/list]
[small][b]Collection Conduct:[/b] Any on-site recovery action must remain within applicable law and corporate policy; “reasonable force” does not authorize irreparable injury or lethal action. Borrower agrees that refusal to comply with recovery directives constitutes continued Default and triggers additional fees.[/small]
[hr][b]8. Privacy, Records & Disclosures (One-Way)[/b]
[list]
[*]Borrower acknowledges Idris maintains account and transaction records for servicing, underwriting, oversight, fraud prevention, and compliance.
[*]Borrower authorizes verification of employment, income, duty status, and access/assignment details as necessary to service this loan.
[*]Borrower authorizes sharing of delinquency status with the employer’s authorized finance/administration contacts where wage deduction or access control is relevant.
[*]Notes / Disclosures (optional): [field]
[/list]
